  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q000952.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) When Ur-Namma , the powerful man , king of Urim , king of Sumer and Akkad , built the temple of Enlil , then for Nanna , the firstborn child of Enlil , his master , he dug the canal whose name is \" Nanna is the canal inspector \", a boundary canal , extending it into the sea . By the just decision of Utu , he examined ( the canal’s course ) and approved it ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000952.19",
      "line_range": "19",
      "translation": "(ii 1) If anyone contest Nanna over ( the canal ) , may he be king or a ruler , he should be treated as if he were cursed by Nanna ! May he lose status in the dwelling of Nanna ! May his city expel him from under the reed canopy ! May his life be miserable !"
    }
  ],
